  "prompt": "I have forgotten ssc cgl password, what should I do now?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your SSC CGL (Staff Selection Commission Combined Graduate Level) exam password, you can reset it by following these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the Official SSC Website**:\n   Go to the official SSC website where you initially registered for the exam.\n\n2. **Access the Login Page**:\n   Navigate to the login page for the SSC CGL where you would normally enter your credentials.\n\n3. **Click on \u2018Forgot Password\u2019**:\n   Look for the \"Forgot Password\" link on the login page and click on it.\n\n4. **Provide Required Details**:\n   You will typically be asked to enter details like your registration ID, and possibly other information like your registered email address or mobile number.\n\n5. **Verification**:\n   You may need to complete a verification process. This could be through a verification code sent to your registered email address or mobile number.\n\n6. **Set a New Password**:\n   Once verification is complete, follow the prompts to set a new password. Make sure to choose a strong password that you will remember.\n\n7. **Login with New Password**:\n   Use your new password to log in to your SSC account.\n\nIf you encounter issues during this process, or if you do not receive the verification code, you should contact SSC support or the helpline provided on the official SSC website for further assistance.\n\nAlways ensure that you keep your login details secure and updated for future reference.",
